<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100751803635193></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100751803635193><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100751803635193>My leveling chart.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100751803635193#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 9:07 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well i have had alot of lower level magicians asking me where did you level / when did you solo or group so i am going to try to awnser the questions and tell you all what i have done.<br> <br>1-4 i stayed in Felwithe being a high elf hunting around there using the nuke then stab to death methods since i didnt have a pet.<br><br>4-8 i went to orc hill in Kelethin and killed wandering orcs in that area, i collected orc belts to turn in for exp on way to Freeport at 8.  I mostly used water pet my whole time soloing until OT, wish i woulda started around LOIO soloing, would have been easier.  water at 4-8 is good idea i believe because not much life difference at this low of level.<br><br>8-13 i hunted in Northern desert of Ro, i soloed at the wizard spires pulling scarabs and spiders unless i found a dervish cuttroat group.   i used water here, cant tell much difference between water and earth this low, and earth over-roots at lower levels.<br><br>13-17 i was in Oasis soloing caimans and wandering mobs or in orc highway groups until 16, when i sat at orc highway next to the groups pulling one mob at a time for at least a blue bar of exp per kill. i would have used earth but this being my first magician i used water.<br><br>17-20 i went to Overthere in kunark at the mudpit, bound and for the most part got a group, soloing when groups not available. try to use earth when soloing.<br><br>20-29 Might seem like a long time in Lake of ill omen but it was great exp, i soloed the whole time.  I mostly stayed right near the windmill pulling tigers and goblins and skeletons roaming around.  at 24 i started camping the skeleton ruins next to the windmill, i would med a good distance away until i got mana, stand up and look for possible adds. if there wasnt any i would burnout and Damage shield pet and nuke one of the skeletons there. they do not help each other unless you are really close and dont add up when you pull, take him out and med for next.  their spawn time is quick enough that you shouldnt ever have to wait for a spawn, so ideal exp. i stayed here until 29.  try to use earth, burnout and damage sheild pet before.  when i started here i used water and never used a damage shield, it makes a BIG difference.<br><br>29-39  I was in Overthere again next to the frontier mountains zone. from 29-34 it is possible to solo but not worth it. i grouped until 34 when i got new spells and was possible to solo.  If you are a good race you have to watch out for dragoons that wander out from the outpost, they dont hit much harder than quading for 160 except general, but still kills you off very quickly. i would go over to the southwest corner and pull one blue/even mob with pet damage shield and burnout II.  i soloed from 34-39 and the hell level was pretty sucky, took at least 10 hours solo to get out of it for me.  i would use earth pet with damage shield+burnout+ a cold stone for AC, here is when i started using earth pets.<br><br>39-45  Ahh my favorite leveling place in the entire world of norrath, Dreadlands Yeti caves.<br> These give insane Exp for a magician, and no groups form there from long spawn time.  at 39-43 you got to be careful.  I would get a earth pet out and damage shield him, give him burnout.  when you enter caves there is usually a wondering one that spawns every 16.5 minutes that you have to be careful of. kill him off and walk until you find a intersection. on the left there is one standing yeti, forward is a small cave of 4 yeti, and right is a cave of 3.  kill the one just on left then work way to either cave you wish.  Sit at entrance and get pet ready, pull one with malise and send in pet, nuke when tundra yeti at 75 percent health, then again at 25 percent health to be safe.  the cave yeti can double for 76 damage usually and drop essense of winder and frosty datura often. rare drops are gems like black pearl.  The damage shield does the most damage to the yeti cause we have 19 damage  shielding on pet.  you can pick them all off one at a time and go back and forth between caves killing as much as you want. at 44 and 45 i just used a fire pet with Burnout II, pulled with malisement, and nuked once, then just medded up for next. very easy.<br><br>from 45-49 i went back to LOIO.  In the middle of the lake there are bloodgills goblins that you can kill. 12 spawns in all and you just mostly work way around fortress. i used fire pet because he seemed to live longest, burnout II him, DS. i pulled with malisement and nuked once or twice like in tundra yetis. <br>Another choice you have is to camp oowomp in timorous deep or specs/sand giants in oasis. oowomp can drop the +5 int batskull earrings and +5 wisdom braclets as loot and good exp, i spent two levels here in 4 days gaining 3kpp in loot also but he is almost always camped.<br>49-51 i cant really remember what i did, i did alot of guards in butcherblock  and freeport but i dont know if you would like to ruin factions as i did, i camped mostly in freeport, sitting next to Nfp entrance taking guards as they pop.  at 51-54  i did seafury cyclops for a bit and wizards in neriak because of low spawn time, less life, and less mana used, a fun camp but every once and a while someone will have epic pet parked at wizard spawns and AFK for actual days, i feel like training these people. but owell. im level 55 now and still camping wizards, new patch makes you able to camp them up to level 60 :)<br><br>Thats my leveling guide, it is prolly missing alot of information but its around 3:00 AM right now and i am very tired and about to go to bed.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
