	   <tr><td colspan=2>Zuranthium, Staff of Fire Elemental Mastery drops from the Mistress of Scorn in Hate.<br><br>Also, one easy way to get IG/FG toes for the focus quests is Gornit in OOT, he drops all types of toes.<br><br>You may want to edit the bit about soloing yard trash in Unrest until level 20 since all the yard spawns are no XP green at 17 with the exception of the higher level Jackolanterns (Which are very rare btw) At 20 the first floor of the house starts grrening and XP becomes nearly impossibe to get for a while without a harmony puller. A second floor train once forced me (33 mage at the time) a 31 paladin, a 29 ranger, and a 49 (Yes, 49) cleric to zone.<br><br>XP in Kedge Keep is great with a nice group, but usually you need to get a group of guildies because as you said, it's underpopulated.<br><br>The staves of elemental mastery do not particularly increase the power of a pet, they simply add one level instead of increasing it's stats as regular focus items do. Also, they only work on pets using the post-50 summon spells. They are mostly just good for turning in for your epic.<br><br>Earth staff no longer drops from Innoruuk. It now drops VERY RARELY from Magi P'Tasa.<br><br>You CANNOT kill specs, SGs, or HGs solo at level 34. Even at 39 they are very difficult. (Of course, ignore his if you were referring to grouping them) They are also very slow XP because they are tough for their level. The loot is very nice however.<br><br>Because of the nerf on pet proc rates giving gnoll hide lariats to pets is pretty much a waste since pets hardly ever proc anymore (Except for air pets because of their high dex)<br><br>Phantom armor is a really useful spell even when you're not fighting hard mobs as the regen allows me to regenerate health very quickly. I often end up taking 10-40% damage in a given battle from being hit while pulling or accidentaly overaggroing (not hard with the level 34 bolt DD)<br><br>This isn't a complaint or troll (on the contrary your guide helped me out quite a bit when I was a newbie) it just needs some editing :-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
