<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100635699633943></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100635699633943><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100635699633943>Pulling Tip</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100635699633943#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=3768><span id= >Limbripper</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 21st 10:36 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A quick tip I havent seen mentioned before to pull static spawn points with multiple creatures.  I have been using the bolt spell at extreme range to pull one creature out of a group.  I first used this against the six or seven goblins lined up in front of Drooga.  I get up on the zone wall.  Get way far back, try to cast, take one step forward, try to cast, etc. Do this until your bolt spell is in range.  When your bolt is enroute, take a couple of steps backwards.  The aggro is so small at this range that you will only pull the creature hit.  I am now using this to single pull giants from the FV corner camp at lvl 46.  A couple of tips.  Use the lowest lvl bolt spell, I think the reduced amount of damage helps (guessing).  Also, have gate ready (as always) in case you get multiple pulls.  Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

