	   <tr><td colspan=2>Struggling with group communication skills (can you tell that I'm new? hehe)...<br><br>I've seen a pretty even split on calling out mana levels with 'wait until asked' at the one extreme and 'spam the group channel every time it changes by 5 percent' at the other extreme.  My personal preference is to announce mana as soon as the encounter is over (short, sweet, gives everyone a reality check on what that mob cost us) as well as announcing that I'm now medding (even if I had already been medding before the mob dropped).  Unless I was really low on mana and it's a long meditate session, I don't announce again until I'm full of mana (or close enough).<br><br>I've also started announcing mana mid-battle in situations where I'm burning more than usual.  So, if we've been taking encounters and only using 20 or 30m and suddenly I'm down to 50m I'll announce that to let my group know that this encounter is approaching the danger line (a.k.a. we need to end this soon or consider evac if things keep going downhill).  I'm aware that those mana reports will likely get lost in the battle spam.<br><br>Now, my big question is what sort of actions should I announce to the group in group-chat?  Especially, actions that I've tied to a hot-key?  I didn't have any, but spent some time before camping playing with my hot-keys and here's what I'm going to try (yes, I feel like using CAPS is shouting, but I hope it makes it stand out in the battle spam).  BTW, this is my key-bank for when I'm not the puller:<br><br>1) 'pet attack' key - it will say 'PET ATTACKING %T'<br>2) 'pet back off' key - it will say 'PET BACK OFF OF %T'<br>3) 'incoming' key - says 'INCOMING %T' (I figure I'll use this to announce adds<br>4) 'attacking' key - says 'ATTACKING %T' (I use this to announce that I'm going to nuke a target, it's solely a /gsay message)<br>5) 'yell' key - says 'HELP I'm being attacked by %T' (to let the melees know that a mob has found me)<br><br>I figure I can type any other messages (and I'm out of room in the hot-key bank).<br><br>Are there any messages that I should have pre-canned?  (If I was pulling, I would have a 'PULLING %T' key as well)  Do these messages help in the middle of a battle?<br><br>I've not put a '/yell' in my group 'yell' command, because I figure that would encourage other players that wander by to jump in and start wailing on the mob.  I look at '/yell' as 'I don't care if you come and kill steal me, just save my hide from being killed' where in a group encounter we should have the resources in-group to take out anything that aggro's a caster.<br><br>One of the things that I'm having trouble getting across to the players that I've been grouping with is the importance of announcing events in the chat window.  (Case in point, we were camping derv 1 in N Ro, the battle for the 3 easy pops had finished and I had sat down to meditate.  I announced '50m medding' and was far enough away from the camp that I didn't see the battle spam.  I did see 'dorn' pop up on the screen, but figured they were just announcing the pop so we could start getting ready.  By the time I figured out that the wizard was not just casting her buff, the two melees were down a good bit on health.  We took Dorn out, but it the melees were down to 15-20h for no good reason.  I of course apologized and settled for obliquely hinting that someone should've shouted something in the chat window.)<br>&nbsp;<br>Vorish of Morell-Thule, High Elf Mage lvl 20<br>Corish of Morell-Thule, High Elf Cleric lvl 9</td></tr>
