	   <tr><td colspan=2>Assuming I'm interpreting your spelling correctly, correct me if I misunderstood something....<br><br>Invis and shielding are completely different. They can stack, so it's possible to have BOTH on. However, invis KEEPS you from being attacked. You can go through hostile areas in which you would normally be crushed (Kael comes to mind here) I can run through Kael, for example, when invised. But if i said "Oh, I'm shielded, I can take it!" I get smashed by triple 150's, which my 600hp shielded simply cannot take. However, shielding protects me in a combat stuation because if I mess up and get aggro'ed I might survive long enough for my pet to pull it off.<br><br>Hope this helps, I need to get to bed, hope I didn't forget anything :-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
