	   <tr><td colspan=2>this is just my two cp for a lvl 30 mage.<br><br>1)gate<br>ULTRA important. NEVER be without this memmed.<br><br>1)high damage dd<br>doesn't really matter witch pre 30. in my experience just go with what does the most damage.<br>keep in mind that bolt spells DO occasionally double hit. Don't know why, but it works. However if you have something that can do more damage on a single hit than a bolt spell go with that. Also, watch for over nuking, just hit once at the start, then once when they get down to half life. otherwise you end up with an extremely pissed off mob.<br><br>3)debuff<br>malaise line. Helps you and any other casters, particularly nifty because it stacks with tash.<br><br>4)AoE<br>be careful with this one. only use it when there are two or more mobs, and prepare to catch aggro unless they both mobs have a tank on em.<br><br>5)pet heal<br>ULTRA important spell. For soloing more than anything else, if I had a nickle for every time this spell has saved my arse...<br><br>6)Damage shield<br>fairly obvious. just toss it on whoever is taking the hits. Mage damage shield are better than most druid ones, if ya got a wizzy tho, let him.<br><br>7)variant<br>ok, soon as I log in I use slots 6 and 7 to start my EQ day. Self armor buffs (these last a while so don't bother keeping them memmed in battle, just refresh when they fade), food conjuring, coldstones, you get the idea.<br><br>8)pet spell<br>when I first summon it I go with summoned weapons and expedience in slots 6 and 7, then switch them out for burnout and the DS. burnout is MUCH more important than expedience in a battle. It's a difference between casting haste on your pet and casting sow on it. Keep it buffed with expedience, but burnout comes first.<br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre. The Mad Mage of Povar<br><br>30th season<br><br>Edit: also, may wanna mem two different based DDs later on. could come in handy for exploiting resists. Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
