	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here is the config I usually used when I played my magician:<br><br>1. Peronsal Buff<br>2. Damage Shield<br>3. Summon Pet<br>4. Biggest Nuke<br>5. Second Biggest Nuke<br>6. Third Biggest Nuke (used for when mana is very low)<br>7. Malise<br>8. Gate<br><br>That was the config I used with the magician I played before pet healing spells were released. Once they came out with the pet healing spells I was playing my second magician, and at that point I only memmed two DD's at a time in favor of the heal spell. In some situations,however, the heal spell is pretty pointless and you are better off just memming the 3rd nuke. Before you get malise, just keep burnout memmed instead. Also, I highly suggest that you ALWAYS keep gate in the 8th spot. There are two reasons for this. First of all, gate is one of the only ways you can live if your pet just died and you still have the monster on you. Second of all, when you get charmed by a monster, you can still cast the spell in your 8th slot, and gate it is definately good to have in there. Hope that helps.<br><br>Former EQ Addict that is playing again.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
